[{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/#Tutorials","page":"Tutorials","text":"","title":"Tutorials"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/#Simulating-Coupled-Dynamics","page":"Tutorials","text":"using QIENO, Random\n\nL = [1.0 -1.0; -1.0 1.0]\nop = EntropicOperator(L; dissipation=0.05, noise=0.01)\npath = simulate(op, [1.0, -1.0]; steps=20, rng=MersenneTwister(1))\nevaluate_stability(op, path[:, end])","title":"Simulating Coupled Dynamics"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/#Building-a-Hypergraph-Operator","page":"Tutorials","text":"Columns of the incidence matrix represent hyperedges.\n\nusing QIENO\n\nH = [1.0 1.0; 1.0 0.0; 0.0 1.0]\nL = hypergraph_laplacian(H)\nop = EntropicOperator(L)","title":"Building a Hypergraph Operator"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/#Training-an-Interference-Network","page":"Tutorials","text":"Training data is column-major: every column is one sample.\n\nusing QIENO, Random\n\nrng = MersenneTwister(2)\nmodel = QIENONetwork(3; depth=2, coupling=zeros(3, 3), rng=rng)\nx = randn(rng, 3, 32) .* 0.2\ny = tanh.(x)\nlosses = train!(model, x, y; epochs=10)\nlosses[end]","title":"Training an Interference Network"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/#Optional-CUDA-Extension","page":"Tutorials","text":"When CUDA.jl is installed and loaded, transfer a model with:\n\nusing QIENO, CUDA\ngpu_model = to_device(model, Val(:cuda))","title":"Optional CUDA Extension"},{"category":"section","location":"theory/#Theory","page":"Theory","text":"","title":"Theory"},{"category":"section","location":"theory/#Entropic-Dynamics","page":"Theory","text":"For a state vector x in mathbbR^n, QIENO uses the stochastic model\n\ndx_t = left(f_t - gamma x_t - Lx_tright)dt + sigma dW_t\n\nwhere L is a graph or hypergraph coupling operator, gamma is local dissipation, f_t is external forcing, and sigma controls stochastic excitation. simulate integrates this equation with Euler-Maruyama.\n\nThe entropy-production surrogate is\n\ndot S(x) = fracgamma x_2^2 + max(x^top Lx 0)T\n\nThe max guard preserves a non-negative diagnostic even when users provide a coupling matrix that is not numerically positive semidefinite. A physically motivated model should still use a validated Laplacian or comparable operator.","title":"Entropic Dynamics"},{"category":"section","location":"theory/#Quantum-Inspired-Layers","page":"Theory","text":"Each real-valued interference layer computes\n\nh = tanhleft(Wh + Usin(phi odot h) + bright)\n\nThe sinusoidal phase path borrows interference-like structure but does not simulate quantum hardware or claim quantum advantage.","title":"Quantum-Inspired Layers"},{"category":"section","location":"theory/#Limitations","page":"Theory","text":"The current integrator is fixed-step Euler-Maruyama.\nThe stability score is a bounded heuristic, not a calibrated probability.\nDense matrices limit very large graph workloads.\nComparative accuracy and speed claims require domain-specific benchmarks.","title":"Limitations"},{"category":"section","location":"#QIENO.jl","page":"Home","text":"QIENO.jl provides experimental building blocks for studying instability in complex coupled dynamical systems. The package combines stochastic simulation, graph and hypergraph geometry, a quantum-inspired interference network, and an entropy-production stability surrogate.\n\nPages = [\"theory.md\", \"tutorials.md\", \"API.md\"]\nDepth = 2","title":"QIENO.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/Ciprian-LocalPulse/QIENO.jl\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Research-Status","page":"Home","text":"The package is an early-stage research implementation. Its output should be treated as a model-dependent signal, not a guarantee or a certified control decision. Domain validation and uncertainty calibration remain essential.","title":"Research Status"},{"category":"section","location":"API/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"API/#Entropic-Dynamics","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Entropic Dynamics"},{"category":"section","location":"API/#Networks","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Networks"},{"category":"section","location":"API/#Utilities","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Utilities"},{"category":"type","location":"API/#QIENO.EntropicOperator","page":"API Reference","text":"EntropicOperator(coupling; temperature=1, dissipation=0.05, noise=0.01)\n\nThermodynamically constrained operator for a graph-coupled stochastic system. coupling is normally a positive-semidefinite graph or hypergraph Laplacian.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.EntropicOperator"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.entropy_production","page":"API Reference","text":"Return the instantaneous non-negative entropy-production surrogate.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.entropy_production"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.entropic_drift","page":"API Reference","text":"Compute deterministic drift under dissipation, coupling, and external forcing.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.entropic_drift"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.step!","page":"API Reference","text":"Advance a state in place with one Euler-Maruyama step.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.step!"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.simulate","page":"API Reference","text":"Simulate a stochastic trajectory, returning states as columns.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.simulate"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.evaluate_stability","page":"API Reference","text":"evaluate_stability(op, x)\n\nMap entropy production to a bounded score in (0, 1]; larger values indicate lower instantaneous dissipation relative to state energy.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.evaluate_stability"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.hypergraph_laplacian","page":"API Reference","text":"Construct a normalized hypergraph Laplacian from a vertex-edge incidence matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.hypergraph_laplacian"},{"category":"type","location":"API/#QIENO.QuantumLayer","page":"API Reference","text":"A real-valued, quantum-inspired interference layer.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.QuantumLayer"},{"category":"type","location":"API/#QIENO.QIENONetwork","page":"API Reference","text":"A stack of interference layers coupled to an entropic stability operator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.QIENONetwork"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.predict","page":"API Reference","text":"Run a state through every quantum-inspired layer.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.predict"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.train!","page":"API Reference","text":"train!(network, inputs, targets; epochs=100, learning_rate=1e-2)\n\nTrain on column-major samples with deterministic full-batch gradient descent. Returns the mean-squared-error history.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.train!"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.standardize","page":"API Reference","text":"Standardize each feature row and return (transformed, mean, scale).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.standardize"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.rmse","page":"API Reference","text":"Root-mean-square error between equal-sized arrays.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.rmse"},{"category":"function","location":"API/#QIENO.to_device","page":"API Reference","text":"Keep an object on the CPU. Optional extensions add other devices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"QIENO.to_device"}]
